---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of use"
  description="The terms covering the Bundle website and waitlist. Bundle is pre-launch, these terms do not cover investment services, because none are live yet."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of use"
    lead="Last updated: 6 July 2026 · These terms cover this website and waitlist, not investment services (none are live yet)."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose reveal">
        <h2>About these terms</h2>
        <p>
          These terms apply to bundle.ai, this website, and to the waitlist
          you can join through it. By using the site you agree to them. They
          are deliberately short, because the site does one simple thing: it
          explains what we are building and lets you register interest.
        </p>

        <h2>What Bundle is today</h2>
        <p>
          Bundle Technologies Ltd is a pre-launch company. No investment
          services are live. This site describes a product in development and
          publishes educational content about startup investing. Nothing on it
          is investment advice, a personal recommendation, an offer, or a
          financial promotion of any specific investment. Joining the waitlist
          commits you to nothing: it does not open an account, reserve an
          investment, or oblige either of us to anything beyond launch updates.
        </p>

        <h2>Educational content disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The Academy, portfolio frameworks and other educational material are
          general education, not advice. They do not take your circumstances
          into account and are never a recommendation to invest in anything.
          Startup investing is high risk: your capital is at risk, most
          early-stage companies fail, and you should not invest money you
          cannot afford to lose. Tax reliefs such as SEIS and EIS depend on
          your individual circumstances and may change. If you are unsure
          whether startup investing is right for you, speak to a regulated
          financial adviser.
        </p>

        <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>
          Use the site lawfully and considerately. Do not attempt to breach its
          security, scrape it at scale, misrepresent who you are, submit
          malicious code, or use our content to market investments unlawfully.
          We may suspend or block access where we reasonably believe these
          terms are being broken.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          The Bundle name, mark, site design and content belong to Bundle
          Technologies Ltd or its licensors. You are welcome to read, to quote
          briefly with attribution, and to share links. Please do not republish
          substantial parts of the site, or use them commercially, without our
          written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>Liability</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing in these terms excludes or limits any liability that cannot
          lawfully be excluded, including liability for fraud, or for death or
          personal injury caused by negligence. Subject to that, the site and
          its content are provided “as is” and without warranties, and we are
          not liable for losses arising from reliance on the site’s content,
          from investment decisions you make, or from the site being
          occasionally unavailable.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We will update these terms as Bundle develops, most obviously if and
          when regulated services launch with their own terms and disclosures.
          The “last updated” date above will always tell you when. Material
          changes will be flagged to waitlist members by email.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the law of England and Wales, and the
          courts of England and Wales have exclusive jurisdiction over any
          dispute arising from them.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms:
          <a href="mailto:legal@bundle.ai">legal@bundle.ai</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
